National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan held meetings with Saudi Prime Minister and Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman, UAE National Security Advisor Sheikh Tahnoon bin Zayed Al Nahyan, and National Security Advisor of India Ajit Doval in Saudi Arabia. The purpose of the meetings was to advance their shared vision of a more secure and prosperous Middle East region interconnected with India and the world. Sullivan also had separate bilateral meetings with the Crown Prince, Sheikh Tahnoon, and Doval to discuss various bilateral and regional matters. The discussions included reviewing progress in talks to consolidate the truce in Yemen, UN-led efforts to end the war, and other issues. Sullivan expressed gratitude to the Crown Prince for Saudi Arabia's support during the evacuation of US citizens from Sudan. The delegations agreed to maintain regular consultations and follow up on the topics discussed. Sullivan also mentioned his plan to consult with Doval at the upcoming Quad Summit in Australia.